  "birth_place": "Kufa",
  "description": "Muslim Arab philosopher, mathematician and physician (c.801–873)",
  "bio": "阿布·優素福·葉爾孤白·本·伊斯哈格·本·薩巴赫·肯迪（阿拉伯語：أبو يوسف يعقوب إبن إسحاق الكندي，拉丁化：Abū Yūsuf Yaʻqūb ibn Isḥāq al-Kindī；約801年—873年），中世紀阿拉伯的著名哲學家、自然科學家。歐洲人稱之為阿爾金杜斯（拉丁語：Alkindus）。他是亞里斯多德學派的主要代表人物之一。他在密碼學方面首次發現了頻率分析的方法，是現代密碼學創始人之一。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "Muslim Arab philosopher, mathematician and physician (c.801–873)",
  "bio_en": "Abū Yūsuf Yaʻqūb ibn ʼIsḥāq aṣ-Ṣabbāḥ al-Kindī (; Arabic: أبو يوسف يعقوب بن إسحاق الصبّاح الكندي; Latin: Alkindus; c. 801–873 AD) was an Arab polymath who was active as a philosopher, mathematician, physician, and music theorist. Al-Kindi was the first of the Islamic peripatetic philosophers, and is hailed as the \"father of Arab philosophy\".\nAl-Kindi was born in Kufa and educated in Baghdad. He became a prominent figure in the House of Wisdom (Bayt al-Hikma), an institute of translation and learning patronized by the Abbasid caliphs, in Baghdad, and a number of Abbasid caliphs appointed him to oversee the translation of Greek scientific and philosophical texts into the Arabic language.",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}